                <dt>Physical Descriptions</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Medium</dt>
              <dd>Bronze</dd>
            
           
                        <dt>Technique</dt>
             <dd>Hammered</dd>
           
                          <dt>Dimensions</dt>
              <dd>diam. 3.9 x l. (of clapper) 2.5 cm (1 9/16 x 1 in.)</dd>
            
                          <dt>Technical Details</dt>
              <dd>
                                                      <p class="divider">Chemical Composition: ICP-MS/AAA data from sample, Bronze:<br />
Cu, 84.16; Sn, 14.66; Pb, 0.19; Zn, 0.02; Fe, 0.21; Ni, 0.03; Ag, 0.05; Sb, 0.09; As, 0.59; Bi, less than 0.025; Co, less than 0.005; Au, less than 0.01; Cd, less than 0.001<br />
<br />
J. Riederer</p>
                                      <p class="divider">Technical Observations: The bell is hammered out of a bronze sheet. The floral decorations that cover much of the surface were created by drawing on the outer surface with a hard, pointed tool. The pressure has distorted the metal sheet and created an impression of the pattern in relief on the inside of the object. Corrosion accretions fill most of the recesses of the decorative pattern, and there is green patina inside and out. The very thin-walled metal form is broken and cracked. There is a broken hole at the top of the shape and the entire rim of the object is frayed or missing. The handle, one end of which is broken off, is held in place by a recent restoration. The iron clapper is heavily corroded. Both handle and clapper may be replacement pieces.         <br />
 <br />
<br />
Francesca G. Bewer</p>
                                                </dd>
            
            
            
            
            
          </dl>
        </dd>
        
